### Q7. What are Props in React?

**Answer:**
Props (short for **Properties**) are a mechanism for passing **data from a parent component to a child component**. They are **read-only** — a child component cannot modify its own props.

```jsx
// Parent Component
function App() {
  return <UserCard name="Manas" age={25} role="Developer" />;
}

// Child Component
function UserCard({ name, age, role }) {
  return (
    <div>
      <h2>{name}</h2>
      <p>Age: {age}</p>
      <p>Role: {role}</p>
    </div>
  );
}
```

**Key points:**
- Props flow **one way** — parent → child (unidirectional)
- Props are **immutable** — the child cannot change them
- You can pass **any data type** — strings, numbers, arrays, objects, functions, even other components
- Use **destructuring** for cleaner syntax: `({ name, age })` instead of `props.name`

