### Q12. What is the `children` prop?

**Answer:**
`children` is a **special prop** that contains whatever you pass **between** the opening and closing tags of a component. It enables **composition** — building components that wrap other components.

```jsx
function Card({ title, children }) {
  return (
    <div className="card">
      <h2>{title}</h2>
      <div className="card-body">{children}</div>
    </div>
  );
}

// Usage — anything between <Card> and </Card> becomes `children`
<Card title="Profile">
  <img src="avatar.jpg" />
  <p>Hello, I'm Manas!</p>
</Card>
```

**Interview tip:** *"The children prop is how React implements composition. It's similar to slots in Vue.js. It allows creating flexible, reusable wrapper components like layouts, cards, modals, etc."*

