### Q13. What is Conditional Rendering in React?

**Answer:**
Conditional rendering means **showing or hiding UI elements** based on certain conditions — just like `if/else` in JavaScript.

**4 ways to do it:**

```jsx
// 1️⃣ if/else (outside JSX)
function Greeting({ isLoggedIn }) {
  if (isLoggedIn) {
    return <h1>Welcome back!</h1>;
  }
  return <h1>Please sign in.</h1>;
}

// 2️⃣ Ternary operator (inline)
return <div>{isLoggedIn ? <Dashboard /> : <Login />}</div>;

// 3️⃣ Logical AND — short circuit (show or nothing)
return <div>{hasNotifications && <Badge count={5} />}</div>;

// 4️⃣ Return null (render nothing)
function Warning({ show }) {
  if (!show) return null;
  return <p>⚠️ Warning!</p>;
}
```

**When to use which:**
| Method        | Use When                                      |
| ------------- | --------------------------------------------- |
| `if/else`     | Multiple conditions, complex logic            |
| Ternary `? :` | Toggle between two elements                   |
| `&&`          | Show something or nothing                     |
| `null`        | Component should render nothing               |

