### Q15. What is the difference between `export default` and `named export`?

**Answer:**

```jsx
// Named export �� import by exact name with { }
export const Button = () => { /* ... */ };
export const Input = () => { /* ... */ };
// Import: import { Button, Input } from './components';

// Default export — import with any name, no { }
const App = () => { /* ... */ };
export default App;
// Import: import App from './App';
// Import: import MyApp from './App';  // works too (any name)
```

| Feature       | Named Export                 | Default Export                |
| ------------- | --------------------------- | ---------------------------- |
| Per file      | Multiple allowed             | Only one allowed             |
| Import syntax | `{ exactName }`             | Any name, no braces          |
| Renaming      | `{ Button as Btn }`        | Automatic (any name)         |
| Use case      | Utility functions, hooks    | Main component of a file     |

