### Q46. What is the difference between SSR, CSR, SSG, and ISR?

**Answer:**

| Method | Full Name                       | When HTML is Generated | Use Case                          |
| ------ | ------------------------------- | ---------------------- | --------------------------------- |
| **CSR** | Client-Side Rendering          | In the browser         | Dashboards, admin panels          |
| **SSR** | Server-Side Rendering          | On each request        | SEO-critical, dynamic content     |
| **SSG** | Static Site Generation         | At build time          | Blogs, docs, marketing pages      |
| **ISR** | Incremental Static Regeneration | Build time + revalidation | E-commerce, news (best of both) |

```
CSR: Server sends empty HTML → JS loads → React renders in browser
SSR: Server renders full HTML per request → sends to browser → hydration
SSG: HTML generated at build time → served from CDN → fastest
ISR: SSG + periodic regeneration (e.g., every 60 seconds)
```

